<!-- 1 Variables, constants, and parameters. Change and variation.
2 Functions, accumulation, and rate of variation. Graphs of functions. Transformations of functions/graphs.
3 Modelling accumulation and rate of variation. Differential equation examples (but no solving).
4 Long-term behaviour: horizontal asymptotes (i.e., informal treatment of limits as x → ∞).
  Singular behaviour: vertical asymptotes (i.e., informal treatment of limits where y →∞).
  Connections to differential equations.
5 Step functions and their graphs. Accumulation when rate function is a step function. Sigma notation.
6 Approximate accumulation from rate of variation (using step functions). Exact accumulation from rate of variation. Polynomial growth (i.e., accumulation when rate of variation is polynomial).
7 Logarithmic growth/decay (i.e., accumulation when rate of variation is 1/x.) Logarithm function: graph, properties, etc.
8 Logistic models, associated differential equations.
9 Exponential growth/decay. Exponential function: graph, properties, etc.
10 Accumulation when rate of variation is exponential. Separable differential equations.
11 Periodic growth/decay. Trig functions: graphs, properties, etc.
12 Models & differential equations where solution is periodic, with examples from the sciences.
13 Average rate of variation. Differentials and approximate rate of variation.
14 Exact rate of variation from approximate rate of variation. Rate of variation formulas (polynomial, logarithmic, exponential, trig).
15 Implicit differentiation. One-to-one and inverse functions. Rate of variation for inverse functions.
16 Average value of a function. Mean Value Theorems. Fundamental Theorem.
17 Chain rule. Reversing the chain rule (substitution).
18 Product rule. Linear differential equations and integrating factors.
19 Higher-order rate functions. Curve-sketching.
20 Local/absolute extremes. Optimization.
21 Autonomous differential equations. -->
